{"application": "software-mentions", "version": "0.8.0", "date": "2024-10-07T12:08+0000", "md5": "A533D0FCDF1C57CED57EE762E7E25A13", "mentions": [{"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SynSem", "normalizedForm": "SynSem", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 6}, "context": "SynSem stays true to the overall approach of ISO 24613:2008, but some simplifications/modifications were introduced. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.02967703342437744}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 6.222724914550781e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9987685084342957}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.973304271697998}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.344650268554688e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SynSem", "normalizedForm": "SynSem", "offsetStart": 4, "offsetEnd": 10}, "context": "The SynSem module allows for the description of syntactic and semantic properties of lexemes, as well as the complex interactions between them. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 3.886222839355469e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.002702772617340088}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9987685084342957}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.973304271697998}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.344650268554688e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SynArgMap", "normalizedForm": "SynArgMap", "offsetStart": 4, "offsetEnd": 13}, "context": "The SynArgMap class can also be used to represent the link between syntactic arguments: in this case the representation tells us that the object in the transitive construction becomes the subject of the intransitive one.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004509270191192627}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 4.9233436584472656e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004509270191192627}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 4.9233436584472656e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SynSem", "normalizedForm": "SynSem", "offsetStart": 19, "offsetEnd": 25}, "context": "Figure 1 gives the SynSem class diagram.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.7602934837341309}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 3.695487976074219e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9987685084342957}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.973304271697998}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.344650268554688e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SynSem", "normalizedForm": "SynSem", "offsetStart": 30, "offsetEnd": 36}, "context": "More precisely, we integrated SynSem components at three specific places within the standard structure of a TEI lexical entry:", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9987685084342957}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0017862319946289062}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9987685084342957}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.973304271697998}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.344650268554688e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SynSem", "normalizedForm": "SynSem", "offsetStart": 43, "offsetEnd": 49}, "context": "In what follows, we shall begin by placing SynSem in the context of the new multipart LMF, and providing an update as to its current status. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.003316223621368408}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.7560577988624573}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9987685084342957}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.973304271697998}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.344650268554688e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SynSemArgMap", "normalizedForm": "SynSemArgMap", "offsetStart": 52, "offsetEnd": 64}, "context": "Linking between syntax and semantics is done by the SynSemArgMap component, which links a Se-manticArgument with a SyntacticArgument.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.46145743131637573}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.3470649719238281e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.46145743131637573}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.3470649719238281e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Syntax", "normalizedForm": "Syntax", "offsetStart": 62, "offsetEnd": 68}, "context": "Then we shall describe the constituent parts of the standard: Syntax, Semantics, and SynSem interface.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.09608447551727295}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.6480216979980469}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.10436785221099854}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.973304271697998}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Syntax", "normalizedForm": "Syntax", "offsetStart": 76, "offsetEnd": 82}, "context": "This short paper introduces one of these new parts, ISO 24613-6, namely the Syntax and Semantics (SynSem) module.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 8.976459503173828e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.973304271697998}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.10436785221099854}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.973304271697998}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SemanticPredicate", "normalizedForm": "SemanticPredicate", "offsetStart": 84, "offsetEnd": 101}, "context": "A PredicativeRepresentation serves to connect a Sense with one or more instances of SemanticPredicate, which are described in terms of SemanticArgument instances. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0010938644409179688}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.9325485229492188e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.45469188690185547}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 5.4717063903808594e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SynSem", "normalizedForm": "SynSem", "offsetStart": 85, "offsetEnd": 91}, "context": "Then we shall describe the constituent parts of the standard: Syntax, Semantics, and SynSem interface. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.09608447551727295}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.6480216979980469}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9987685084342957}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.973304271697998}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.344650268554688e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SemanticPredicate", "normalizedForm": "SemanticPredicate", "offsetStart": 94, "offsetEnd": 111}, "context": "\u2022 We extended the general intermediate of a TEI document to allow <subcategorization-Frame>, <SemanticPredicate> and <SynSem-Correspondence> elements to occur freely and be referred to from <syntacticBehaviour> and <predicativeRepresentation> within entries.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.45469188690185547}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 5.4717063903808594e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.45469188690185547}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 5.4717063903808594e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SynSem", "normalizedForm": "SynSem", "offsetStart": 98, "offsetEnd": 104}, "context": "This short paper introduces one of these new parts, ISO 24613-6, namely the Syntax and Semantics (SynSem) module. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 8.976459503173828e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.973304271697998}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9987685084342957}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.973304271697998}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.344650268554688e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Syntax", "normalizedForm": "Syntax", "offsetStart": 116, "offsetEnd": 122}, "context": "The current paper is dedicated to ISO 24613-6, a soon-to-be published part of the revised LMF standard dealing with Syntax and Semantics (henceforth SynSem), two areas which as we mentioned above were previously covered by separate modules in the old LMF.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "scor